content:
Alright, I'm going to design a responsive HTML/CSS template for a personal portfolio website. The template should include sections for a header, about me, skills, projects, and contact information. It needs to be mobile-friendly and work well on various screen sizes. Also, I'll use JavaScript to add smooth scrolling navigation between sections.

First, I'll start by planning the structure of the HTML file. I need to have a header with a navigation menu, an about me section, a skills section, a projects section, and a contact section. Each section should be clearly marked with an ID so that I can link to them using anchor tags.

Here's a basic outline of the HTML structure:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Personal Portfolio</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header id="header">
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#header">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#skills">Skills</a></li>
                <li><a href="#projects">Projects</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <p>Some text about myself.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="skills">
        <h2>Skills</h2>
        <p>List of skills.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="projects">
        <h2>Projects</h2>
        <p>Details about projects.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Contact information.</p>
    </section>

    <script src="scripts.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

Next, I'll work on the CSS to make the design responsive. I'll use media queries to adjust the layout for different screen sizes. I'll also ensure that the font sizes and spacing are appropriate for mobile devices.

Here's a basic structure for the CSS:

```css
/* styles.css */

* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
}

header {
    background: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
}

nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
}

nav ul li {
    margin: 0 1rem;
}

nav ul li a {
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
}

section {
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
    nav ul {
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    nav ul li {
        margin: 0.5rem 0;
    }
}
```

This CSS sets up a basic layout with a header and navigation menu. The navigation menu is displayed horizontally on larger screens and vertically on smaller screens using a media query.

Now, I'll add some JavaScript to enable smooth scrolling when clicking on the navigation links.

Here's the JavaScript code:

```javascript
// scripts.js

document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]').forEach(anchor => {
    anchor.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
        e.preventDefault();

        document.querySelector(this.getAttribute('href')).scrollIntoView({
            behavior: 'smooth'
        });
    });
});
```

This script selects all anchor tags that have href starting with "#" and adds a click event listener to each. When a link is clicked, it prevents the default behavior and smoothly scrolls to the corresponding section.

To make the template more visually appealing, I can add some styling to the sections, such as background colors, borders, or images. I can also include icons or images to represent skills or projects.

Additionally, for the contact section, I can include a contact form or links to social media profiles.

Overall, this should provide a solid foundation for a responsive personal portfolio website.

**Final Solution**

To create a responsive personal portfolio website, we'll design an HTML template with sections for the header, about me, skills, projects, and contact information. We'll ensure the design is mobile-friendly using CSS media queries and enhance the user experience with smooth scrolling using JavaScript.

